Brief Description:
This presentation dives into Digital Literacy Essentials which is everything students need to handle today's digital world like pros. it takes you from basic browsing to real digital citizenship through three main areas: getting tools right, thinking critically about online information and creating your own content confidently.

Key Topics Covered:

Defining Digital Literacy: Explains what digital literacy actually means for school papers, group projects, job applications.

Essential Student Toolkit: Practical tools that save time—Notion or Evernote for organizing research notes, Google Docs for live team editing, Toggl or Todoist to track assignments and deadlines so nothing slips.

Safe Internet Practices: Real-talk on staying secure—crafting strong passwords (no "password123"), spotting phishing scams before clicking, protecting privacy across apps and sites.

